Stopped by for dinner one night. The BLAST sandwich was awesome, and I love how you can get tater tots as a side. The beer menu leaves a bit to be desired for beer enthusiasts and is a bit pricey (but so is the rest of the booze in Old Town so I can't knock it), however, the staff is super friendly!  All in all, highly recommend if you want a quick bite and a basic beer. No complaints :-)

Here is what I will say - I really enjoy the pizza, and they have Green Line beer, so that is always nice. In the end, though, it is really not a GREAT place. In the summer, they have some outdoor seating, which is nice.  What really brings them down is their drinks and their service. I recommend you get the beer (a very small variety on draft) or wine (again, only two options) because they are super skimpy on their mixed drinks. A friend asked for wine to replace her mixed drink, and without prompting the waiter said he saw the bartender put a lot of liquor in it, and that she should just 'slam it.' Friend didn't bring up the weak pour, so it is clear they understand it is an issue, and instead of addressing it they are just encouraging people to chug their drinks so they don't need to comp them.
The food was great and the service was fast

So I came to this place on a Wednesday night. We were 8 friends. It wasn't packed at all.  All my friends got their pizza's at the same time, however, mine came out 30 minutes late. So instead of eating after everyone was finished I told him the server to cancel my order and void the charges cause I had a tab open. He said it had been voided.  Today I look at my statement and the charges went from pending to official. They charged me for a pizza I never even got to eat. It came out 30 minutes late.  I just don't understand how this could have happened on a night where it wasn't even busy. On top of that you charge me?!?!  Now I have to call my credit card company and report a theft to the police.  Never going back here again just out of principle.  Thank you Justin

The food here is good, but more importantly they serve God's Own Tater Tots.

Living on Wells street, I'm always looking to get away from the douchery that Benchmark and Old Town Pour House attract at night on the weekends (don't get me wrong, I love those places during the week and during the day on the weekends).  I've found solace in Old Town Pub - my neighborhood dive bar! Decent prices, I don't hate the food and we can always find a seat. While the service can be below par, anything is better than relentlessly getting spilled on by a bunch of bros while I push my way the bar only to wait 20 minutes before you can even get the bartenders attention at other Old Town establishments!
Great service, but the food really sucks. If you want the shittiest nachos known to man, go for it.

Cute neighborhood pizza place, with thin crust pizza, al kinds of apps and bar bites and great mac n cheese! They have an extensive beer list, but not nearly as fancy as Old Town Pour House down the street. The interior is a bit dark, but they have lots of TVs and show the games. They also deliver through GrubHub.
Used to live across the street from OTP and go there for bar food all the time.  The pizza is great and salad and sandwiches are pretty good as well.  Really affordable and convenient
